# **WealthGenie – Personal Finance Tracker with AI**

*Track income, expenses, EMIs, savings — and get smart AI suggestions.*

## **Features**

| Feature | Description |
| ----- | ----- |
| **Dashboard** | Real-time summary of income, expenses, and savings |
| **EMI Tracker** | Track loans, installments, due dates |
| **Savings Goals** | Set, monitor, and achieve financial targets |
| **Data Import/Export** | CSV & JSON upload/download |
| **Transaction History** | Filterable, searchable expense log |
| **AI Suggestions** | GROQ-powered financial insights via chatbot |
| **Secure Backend** | Optional Supabase auth & data persistence |

**No backend required** – runs fully offline in demo mode.

## **Tech Stack**

![][image1]

* **Frontend**: React 18 \+ TypeScript  
* **Build Tool**: [Vite](https://vitejs.dev/) (blazing fast HMR)  
* **AI**: [GROQ](https://groq.com/) (llama-3.1-70b-versatile)  
* **Backend (Optional)**: [Supabase](https://supabase.com/)

---

## **Prerequisites**

bash  
Node.js \>\= v18  
npm \>\= 9

Recommended: Use **VS Code \+ Dev Container** (Ubuntu 24.04)

---

## **Local Development**

### **1\. Install Dependencies**

npm install

### **2\. Start Dev Server**

npm run dev

Open: [http://localhost:5173](http://localhost:5173)

From Dev Container:

$BROWSER http://localhost:5173

### **3\. Build for Production**

npm run build

### **4\. Preview Production Build**

npm run preview  
---

## **Environment Configuration (Optional)**

### **GROQ API**

1. Get your key from [console.groq.com](https://console.groq.com)

Edit:

// src/utils/groq/config.ts

2. export const GROQ\_API\_KEY \= "your-key-here";  
3. See: GROQ\_API\_SETUP.md

### **Supabase**

1. Create project at [supabase.com](https://supabase.com)

Add env vars in .env.local or server function:  
env  
`SUPABASE_URL=your-supabase-url`

2. `SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key`  
3. Example server function: src/supabase/functions/server/index.tsx

**No keys?** App runs in **demo mode** (localStorage, stubbed AI).

## **Development Tips**

* Use **Vite HMR** for instant UI updates  
* Open **DevTools → Network** to debug GROQ/Supabase calls  
* Check terminal for exact local URL  
* AI responses cached in localStorage during dev

---

## **Troubleshooting**

| Problem | Fix |
| ----- | ----- |
| Module not found | Run npm install and restart |
| AI not responding | Check GROQ\_API\_KEY and network |
| Supabase 401 | Verify SUPABASE\_ANON\_KEY |
| Page not opening | Run $BROWSER http://localhost:5173 |
